With Pick, select the item or items you want by using the arrow keys or "h", 
"j", "k", and "l" to highlight the item you want to select and press "t" or
space to toggle the selection. You can also use the mouse to click on items
to select or deselect them. When you are done, press "Enter" to accept the 
selections. If you want to cancel and exit without making any selections,
press "q" or F9. For more information, press F1 or "H" to display this help 
message again.

If pick is configured to accept only one selection, then selecting an item
will automatically trigger acceptance. Otherwise, you can select multiple
items and then press "Enter" or F10 to accept them all at once.

If an external executable is specified on the command line, pick will
execute the command on acceptance. he pick If an output file is specified
on the command line, pick will write the selected items to the file on 
acceptance.
